Circular economy. Green economy. Circular design. The role and importance of the environment in design and society.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the students' business skills and make them ponder about the sustainable use of natural resources to meet the renewed demands of consumers and markets for the provision of environmentally friendly, natural, healthy products and services that create maximum value for different parties.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student will:  1) understand the concepts and essence of circular design, green consumer society and sustainable consumption, consumer needs and the resulting business opportunities; 2) understand the concept and importance of supply chain management; 3) be able to take into account the principles of circular design and green economy when developing new services (or products); 4) understand the difference between local and international business, target market definitions, segmentation and cost-benefit analysis.
